Moldavia agreed on Sunday to comply with the Kremlin's order to reconsider its law  making the Moldavian language the republic's official language.
Moldavia borders  Romania, and the Moldavian language is identical to Romanian except for the Cyrillic  script that Stalin imposed on the republic.
Gorbachev gave Moldavia ten days to fashion  measures insuring the rights of minorities.
A group 150,000 Turkish Christians, and  groups of Russians and Ukrainians living in Moldavia claim to be victims of  discrimination.
They want autonomy.
Hard-liners want Gorbachev to declare a state of  emergency in the ethnically and geographically diverse republic. 
